2.3 로지스틱 회귀모형

2.4 로지스틱 회귀 모형

\[\begin{align} \begin{split} default_i & \ind Ber(\pi(balance_i), ~ i=1,2, \ldots, n \\ \pi(balance_i) & = logistic (\beta_0 + \beta_1 \times balance_i) = \frac{e^{\beta_0 + \beta_1 \times balance_i}}{1+e^{\beta_0 + \beta_1 \times balance_i}} \\ \pi(\beta_0, \beta_1) d\beta_0 d\beta_1 & = 1 \times d\beta_0 d\beta_1 \end{split} \end{align}\]

default.logistic1.code ="
data {
  int<lower=0> n;
  int<lower=0, upper=1> defaults[n];
  vector[n] balance;
}

parameters {
  real alpha;
  real beta;
}

model {
  for(i in 1:n) {
    defaults[i] ~ bernoulli_logit(alpha + beta * balance[i]);
  }
}
"

data=list(n=dim(Default)[1], defaults=as.integer(as.numeric(Default$default)-1), balance=Default$balance)

default는 STAN의 내부 예약어라서 변수명을 default로 쓰면 에러가 난다. 변수 명을 defaults로 바꾸면 돌아간다.

default.logistic1 = stan(model_code=default.logistic1.code, data=data, seed=1234567, chains=1, iter=5000, thin=1, cores=4)

3 포아송 회귀모형

Lunn, D., Jackson, C., Best, N., Spiegelhalter, D., & Thomas, A. (2012). The BUGS book: A practical introduction to Bayesian analysis. Chapman and Hall/CRC. 이 책의 Example 6.5.2. Count data: Salmonella.

\[y_{ij} \sim Poi(\mu_i), ~ \log \mu_i = \alpha + \beta \log(x_i + 10) + \gamma x_i.\] 평균함수의 그림

x = seq(from=0, to= 1200, length.out = 200)
a = 2.13
b = 0.33
c = -0.001
log.mu = a + b*log(x+10) + c*x
mu = exp(log.mu)
df = data.frame(x=x, mu=mu, log.mu = log.mu)
df %>% ggplot(aes(x=x,y=log.mu)) + geom_line()

df %>% ggplot(aes(x=x,y=mu)) + geom_line()

#자료 
y = t(matrix(c(15, 16, 16, 27, 33, 20, 21, 18, 26, 41, 38, 27, 29, 21, 33, 69, 41, 42), nr=3, byrow=TRUE) )
x = c(0,10,33,100,333,1000)
pois.code ="
data {
  real<lower=0> x[6];
  int<lower=0> y[6,3];
}

parameters {
  real alpha;
  real beta;
  real gamma; 
}

model {
  for(i in 1:6) {
    for(j in 1:3) {
      y[i,j] ~ poisson(exp(alpha+beta*log(x[i] +10) + gamma*x[i]));
    }
  }
}
"

data=list(x=x, y=y)
pois = stan(model_code = pois.code, data=data, seed = 123456789, chains = 1, iter = 10000, thin=10, cores=4)
